org.sbml.jsbml.util.compilers
Class FormulaCompiler

java.lang.Object
  org.sbml.jsbml.util.StringTools
      org.sbml.jsbml.util.compilers.FormulaCompiler
All Implemented Interfaces:
ASTNodeCompiler
Direct Known Subclasses:
FormulaCompilerNoPiecewise, LibSBMLFormulaCompiler
public class FormulaCompiler
extends StringTools
implements ASTNodeCompiler

This class creates C-like infix formula Strings that represent the content of ASTNodes. These can be used to save equations in SBML with older than Level 2.

Since:
0.8
Version:
$Rev: 1358 $
Author:
Alexander Dörr, Andreas Dräger

public ASTNodeValue compile(String name)
Description copied from interface: ASTNodeCompiler
A compiler will also have to deal with a name. The meaning of this can be various. For instance, the name may refer to a Species in the system. In case of numerical computation, the ASTNodeCompiler must create an ASTNodeValue representing the current value of this Species.
